ite news|url=https://www.yugmarg.com/epaper/?dt=2020/02/24&p=4|title=Dream Buds Foundation to support the underprivileged|date= 24 February 2020|accessdate= 25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.facebook.com/Diljott/ Diljott Facebook]\n* [http://instagram.com/diljott/ Diljott Instagram]\n* [https://twitter.com/Diljott/ Diljott Twitter]\n* [http://www.diljott.com/ Diljott Website]\n* [http://www.snapchat.com/add/diljottofficial/ Diljott Snapchat]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/c/DILJOTTofficial/ You Tube Channel]\n* {{IMDb name|8420520}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Diljott}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian actresses]]\n[[Category:Indian film actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Punjabi cinema]]\n[[Category:Indian women philanthropists]]\n[[Category:Indian philanthropists]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Punjab, India]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Indian English|date=September 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Diljott\n| image              = Wikipedia.jpg\n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = Diljott\n| birth_date         = \n| birth_place        = \n| occupation         = Actress, singer, philanthropist\n| nationality        = Indian\n| years_active       = 2014\u2013present\n| height             = \n| parents            = \n| relatives          = \n| education          = Masters in Human Rights (University Gold Medalist), <br /> Bachelors in Psychology Honors (University Gold Medalist),<br /> Post Graduate Course in NGO Management\n}}\n\n'''Diljott''' is an Indian film actress, singer and a philanthropist. She won attention for her lead roles in films like ''Khatre Da Ghuggu'',<ref>{{cite news|title= Up and About Jordan Sandhu and Diljott |url= https://epaper.tribuneindia.com/c/48063559 |newspaper= The Tribune|date= 17 January 2020|accessdate= 18 January 2020}}</ref> [